{
  "texts": [
    "It includes proficiency in AI applications and related products, familiarity with the operating standards of AI tools, and the ability to integrate different types of AI applications and tools to solve specific problems.",
    "The study found that AI usage significantly impacts the effectiveness of participants in using ChatGPT to solve programming problems.",
    "AI evaluation literacy primarily refers to the user's ability to compare similar products and select the optimal solution.",
    "AI ethics literacy refers to the user's concern for ethical issues that AI may raise, such as privacy breaches (Wang et al., 2022).",
    "In this study, there are possible reasons why these two dimensions did not have a significant impact on learners' effectiveness in solving programming problems: firstly, the study specified ChatGPT as the tool for completing the project tasks, eliminating the need for learners to make independent choices; secondly, during the project implementation, a relatively stable and secure ChatGPT environment was provided to learners, aiming to minimize the occurrence of ethical issues."
  ]
}